{
  "stem": "21626.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But Dorothy's cheerful face appeared by the door of the ambulance before they closed it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And she said to me, [NON-ENGLISH], which means au revoir, see you.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So I thought, well, I can't be dying after all.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And when I was in the isolation hospital, Mrs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Campion obviously contacted Mommy Rainford.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And Mommy Rainford came immediately, didn't even take her-- stop to take her apron off.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they both came to this hospital to see me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They weren't allowed inside.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And by then I was already turning somersaults in my bed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But of course, even the little notes we were able to send via Holland then to my parents stopped because I wasn't allowed to write.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I was terribly worried, and they were terribly worried at not hearing from me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So the first thing I did when I came out of hospital was to sit down.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then I know I wrote in desperation in my diary, what can I say?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm not allowed to speak the truth.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm not allowed to mention I'm in England.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, it was so difficult for an 11-year-old kid, and to find the words, how much she misses them, and yet not to make them sad.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But very soon, the letters stopped all together.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as I said earlier, after that, it was my diary and the stars and the sun that I turned to, and also my sis.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We wrote almost daily.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My parents wrote to me daily at first until war started.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Every single day a letter came.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was a wonderful bond, you know, which for many children-- I mean, there were about 669 children came on these transports from Prague.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I, I've met hundreds of them.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
